Most of this code is borrowed from something I found on the interwebs but I
don't remember the source. If you find your code here, and would like attribution
or removal, please contact me at ddollar@gmail.com

1. Drop an empty USB volume onto "Secure USB Initialize.app"
2. Put "Secure USB Handler.scpt" into /Library/Scripts/Folder Action Scripts/
3. Add Secure USB Handler as a folder action on /Volumes
4. SetFile -a V /Volumes/USBVolume

5. Drop a secure USB volume onto "Secure USB Restore.app" to revert, you will
   be prompted to save the secure volume
